Description: Total deaths in February with confirmed linkages to COVID-19, per million population
Total COVID-19 test results returned positive in February, per million population
Average of daily difference between observed deaths and expected deaths in February, per million population
Average daily percentage of respondents to Delphi Pandemic Survey who report wearing a mask most or all of the time while in public, from 9 February to 20 February
Average percent change from baseline of visits to public transit stations in February, according to Google location data
Total number of vaccinations administered by 28 February, per million population
Total COVID-19 test results in February, per million population*

This dataset is a compilation of datasets from various sources. All 50 U.S. states are included. Each line of the dataset provides state identification data, seven variables directly related to COVID-19, and three other variables of interest. Variables related to COVID-19 are aggregates or averages from the month of February 2021.

Variable number: * Due to anomalies in data from Wyoming, total test results for that state includes only test results from February 10 to February 28
